<TITLE> Four university teachers named for UGC as members </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 12 (bdnews24.com) -- Four university teachers have been named for the University Grants Commission as members, officials said Sunday. The nominees are Amena Begum, professor of physics for Dhaka University, Tajul Islam, professor of economics for Jahangirnagar University, Dr AHM Zehadul Karim, teacher of anthropology for Rajshahi University and Abdul Hakim, professor of political science for Chittagong University. A UGC official told bdnews24.com that the four would be appointed on Aug 15. The UGC chairman, Prof Nazrul Islam, told bdnews24.com that the appointments would fill four vacancies left by resignations of as many members. Zehadul Karim said he was informed about the nomination by phone from Dhaka. But he said he did not receive any letter about it On July 31 and Aug 1, four UGC members such as Prof Faisul Islam Faruqui, Prof Mahbubullah, Prof Sultan Hossain Khan and Prof Tarek Shamsur Rehman resigned under clear pressure from the government. Of the five UGC members, Dr Ehsanul Haque stayed on. The UGC chairman justified the resignations saying that the government made the decision. bdnews24.co
